		<div class="postbody">
			<div class="postrow">
				
				
				<h2 class="title icon icon0">
					Re: What is a Mage to YOU!
				</h2>
				

						
						
				<div class="content">
					<div id="post_message_1345698">
						<blockquote class="postcontent restore ">
							<div class="bbcode_container">
	<div class="bbcode_quote">
		<div class="quote_container">
			<div class="bbcode_quote_container"></div>
			
				<div class="bbcode_postedby">
					<img src="images/misc/quote_icon.png" alt="Quote" /> Originally Posted by <strong>CyclopsSlayer</strong>
					<a href="showthread.php?s=9b2f657e51095d52a834430905234931&amp;p=1345460#post1345460" rel="nofollow"><img class="inlineimg" src="images/buttons/viewpost-right.png" alt="View Post" /></a>
				</div>
				<div class="message">Of all the games I have played so far the EQ1 Wiz was probably the prototype of my Caster expectations.<br />
<br />
-Multi elemental attacks so you could usually find the chink in the targets resistances.<br />
-Lower damage, no aggro attacks to allow the caster to assist while the tank(s) lock down aggro.<br />
-High Damage burn capability once the target is safed, or the caster feels suicidal... <img src="images/smilies/smile.gif" border="0" alt="" title="Smilie" class="inlineimg" /><br />
-Squishyness, a 1-2 hit invulnerability followed quickly by laying down next to the ranger <img src="images/smilies/biggrin.gif" border="0" alt="" title="Big Grin" class="inlineimg" /></div>
			
		</div>
	</div>
</div>Good feedback, thanks!<br />
<br />
So, if you had a class with the ability to switch between damage types, cast with subtlety if needed, and unleash the beast when desired, with low defensive capability, you would be satisfied right?<br />
<br />
Does it have to be elemental damage, or would other types work as well?<br />
<br />
<br />
Generally, switching between different elements wont be a huge boon, but on some foes you will get the bonuses.<br />
<br />
The biggest difference will be using Physical or Magical damage spells though, as these each attack different health bars.<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
Right now, the Mage class doesnt have a Path that islike the traditional Wizard,but I think you will find the Druid's Storm Caller Path to have most of your desired playing methods:<br />
<br />
Uses Lightning and Wind to deal magical and physical damage respectively.<br />
<br />
Grows stronger with repeated uses of different lightning or wind spells, each charging up either a Thunderhead or a Cyclone that they have summoned into the area as a Weather Effect.<br />
<br />
Can expend the charged up energy in their Cyclone or Thunderhead for powerful attacks, or hold onto the charge for improved capability on their normal spells.<br />
<br />
While they have very limited self-defense mechanisms, but they don't compromise their own safety while performing their role (some primary DPS classes do, such as my Berserker).<br />
<br />
They will have some method of dealing damage early in the fight with low hate, and then unleashing some full raw power once they've charged up their Thunderhead and/or Cyclone while fighting.<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
Also, I havent fleshed it out as much, but the Elementalist, which is very similar to the eq1 Magician, will have Fire, Ice, Earth, and Air projectile nukes and other similar effects, including a elemental resistance debuff. This will have the elemental nuking concept, if that is most important to you.<br />
<br />
<br />
And the best part, you can be both Paths almost simultaneously, so you can mix and match as you please.
						</blockquote>
					</div>

					
				</div>
			</div>
			
			<div class="cleardiv"></div>
		</div>
	</div>
