		<div class="postbody">
			<div class="postrow">
				
				
				<h2 class="title icon icon0">
					Re: What is a Mage to YOU!
				</h2>
				

						
						
				<div class="content">
					<div id="post_message_1347798">
						<blockquote class="postcontent restore ">
							As you can see, the primary damage source for Primary DPS casters is Resilience, though they can also deal some ok health damage as well.<br />
<br />
Primary DPS Casters will have the &quot;resilience&quot; based Finishers, while Melee DPS Fighters will have the Health based Finishers.<br />
<br />
This is important, because you want to kill the foe quickly while their life is exposed before one of their allies heals them. Instead of peppering the foe's life bar, you could end them in one fell swoop.<br />
<br />
Berserker is an example of a Melee dps Fighter. He has a Decapitate, a Precise type Finisher that cuts off his foe's head, Slaughter, a Power type Finisher that cleaves the foe in two, and Demolish, a Rapid type Finisher that batters your foe into complete ruin.<br />
<br />
Each has a defense that will totally block it, one that will partially block it, and a third that will always avoid it completely, so knowing what your foe's defenses are is important. A landed Finisher will do 1000% damage, a partially mitigated finisher will be reduced to 300% damage, and a avoided finisher will miss. All three types share the same one minute reuse timer, so choose well <img src="images/smilies/smile.gif" border="0" alt="" title="Smilie" class="inlineimg" /><br />
<br />
Power attacks are easily Blocked, moderately Dodged, and cannot be Parried.<br />
<br />
Precise attacks are easily Parried, moderately Blocked, and cannot be Dodged.<br />
<br />
Rapid attacks are easily Dodged, moderately Parried, and cannot be Blocked.<br />
<br />
<br />
So in a nut shell, if your foe's health is down, you want a Melee DPS to finish off its Life swiftly, but if its resilience is down, you want a Primary DPS caster to finish it off with a deadly spell.
						</blockquote>
					</div>

					
				</div>
			</div>
			
			<div class="cleardiv"></div>
		</div>
	</div>
